ice aimed at testing and transforming the limits of shared reality, urgently needed in situations where such reality breaks down or turns precarious. Drawing on pragmatist thought, philosophical aesthetics, and art history, Klinger’s account of Richter’s practice offers a highly distinctive conceptual alternative for contemporary art in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aform, theory of art, contemporary art, philosophical aesthetics, pragmatism, painting, Gerhard Richter.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107391900 cprintz978022634701140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226347295423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226347295/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles